Asparagus facts and tips for growing! ⬇️

- it’s rich in B vitamins, vitamin C, calcium, and iron

- doesn’t require a large amount of space

- it’s a perennial crop, a single planting of asparagus crowns can keep on producing for 20 years or more!

- needs full sun for best production (at least 6-8 hours of sunlight each day

- easiest to establish asparagus by planting 1 to 2 year old crowns (roots)

- you should not harvest any spears until the second year of production
